  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/quick-sweet-chilli-pork-rice-bowl/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pork mince</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 2 min or until starting to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Tip: Add a little vegetable oil if the pan is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/quick-sweet-chilli-pork-rice-bowl/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the<strong> green beans</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/quick-sweet-chilli-pork-rice-bowl/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped green beans</strong> to the<strong> </strong>pork mince and continue to cook for 5-7 min further</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/quick-sweet-chilli-pork-rice-bowl/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>In a small bowl combine the<strong> Chinese rice wine</strong>,<strong> toasted sesame oil</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, and <strong>chilli jam</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> – this is your <strong>sweet chilli sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/quick-sweet-chilli-pork-rice-bowl/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, stir it into the pork pan</p><p>Cook for a further 3-4 min allowing the rice to crisp and brown a bit in the pan</p><p>Chop the <strong>peanuts</strong> roughly</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/quick-sweet-chilli-pork-rice-bowl/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice has started to crisp, remove the pan from the heat and stir in the <strong>sweet chilli sauce </strong>– this is your<strong> sweet chilli pork rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/quick-sweet-chilli-pork-rice-bowl/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sweet chilli</strong> <strong>pork rice</strong> in bowls and garnish with the <strong>chopped peanuts</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
